Acts 13-7 He was with <f>ⓟ</f>the proconsul, Sergius Paulus, a man of intelligence, who summoned Barnabas and Saul and sought to hear the word of God.
Acts 13-8 But Elymas the <f>ⓠ</f>magician (for that is the meaning of his name) <f>ⓡ</f>opposed them, seeking to turn <f>ⓢ</f>the proconsul away from the faith.
Acts 13-9 But Saul, who was also called Paul, <f>ⓣ</f>filled with the Holy Spirit, looked intently at him
