Acts 13-11 And now, behold, <f>ⓨ</f>the hand of the Lord is upon you, and you will be blind and unable to see the sun for a time.” Immediately mist and darkness fell upon him, and he went about seeking <f>ⓩ</f>people to lead him by the hand.
Acts 13-12 Then the proconsul believed, when he saw what had occurred, for he was astonished at <f>ⓐ</f>the teaching of the Lord.
Acts 13-13 <pb/>Now Paul and his companions set sail from Paphos and came to Perga in Pamphylia. And <f>ⓑ</f>John left them and returned <f>ⓒ</f>to Jerusalem,
Acts 13-14 but they went on from Perga and came to Antioch in Pisidia. And <f>ⓓ</f>on the Sabbath day <f>ⓔ</f>they went into the synagogue and sat down.
