Acts 13-24 Before his coming, <f>ⓗ</f>John had proclaimed <f>ⓘ</f>a baptism of repentance to all the people of Israel.
Acts 13-25 And as John was finishing his course, <f>ⓙ</f>he said, ‘What do you suppose that I am? I am not he. No, but behold, after me one is coming, the sandals of whose feet I am not worthy to untie.’
